<DOC><DOCNO> AP881017-0172 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-17-88 2305EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-Obit-Rowny     10-17 0072</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Obit-Rowny,70</SECOND><HEAD>Wife Of Arms Control Adviser Dead At 70</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Mary Rita Rowny, 70, wife of presidential armscontrol adviser Edward L. Rowny, died of cancer Sunday at WalterReed Army Medical Center. She lived in Arlington, Va.   During their 47-year marriage, Mrs. Rowny, a native ofBaltimore, accompanied her husband to assignments in Japan, France,Belgium, Switzerland and West Germany. Survivors include a daughterand four sons.</TEXT></DOC>